OL,3,CNext government 'will need to raise
OL,4,Ctaxes to maintain public services'
OL,6,FThe UK economy grew by 0.1% in 2023
OL,7,Fafter pressure from higher interest
OL,8,Frates and hikes by ratesetters at the
OL,9,FBank of England to slow rampant
OL,10,Finflation.
OL,12,FIn its latest economic outlook report,
OL,13,FNIESR said it forecasts GDP (gross
OL,14,Fdomestic product) will have grown 0.4%
OL,15,Fover the first quarter of 2024 and
OL,16,Fwill rise 0.8% for the year as a
OL,17,Fwhole, compared with 2023.
OL,19,FNevertheless, it said this still
OL,20,Frepresents an "anaemic UK GDP growth
OL,21,Ftrend".
