OL,3,CNext government 'will need to raise
OL,4,Ctaxes to maintain public services'
OL,6,FAdrian Pabst, NIESR deputy director
OL,7,Ffor public policy, said: "While real
OL,8,Fwages are rising, households in the
OL,9,Fbottom half of the income distribution
OL,10,Fcontinue to feel the impact from the
OL,11,Fcost-of-living crisis, with housing
OL,12,Fcosts wiping out the benefits from
OL,13,Fhigher real wages.
OL,15,F"Similarly, the freezing of the
OL,16,Fpersonal allowance and tax bands is
OL,17,Fmaking low and middle-income
OL,18,Fhouseholds worse off despite the cut
OL,19,Fto National Insurance Contributions.
